Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Lesson 34 Adolescence\N\N34  青春期\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.87,0:00:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,First listen and then answer the following question.\N\N听录音,然后回答以下问题.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,adolescent: n.  底毁\N\NWhat do adolescents respect in parents?\N\N青少年尊重父母的什么品质?\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.23,0:00:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents are often upset when their children praise the homes of their friends\N\N当家长听到孩子赞扬自己朋友的家时,总感到不安,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.77,0:00:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,slur: n.  青春期\N\Nand regard it as a slur on their own cooking,or cleaning, or furniture,\N\N认为这是孩子在嫌弃自家的饭菜、卫生、或家具,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.47,0:00:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,adolescent: n.  底毁\N\Nand often are foolish enough to let the adolescents see that they are annoyed.\N\N而且总是会愚蠢地让孩子看出自己的烦恼.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.25,0:00:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,disloyalty: n.  青少年（12-18岁）\N\NThey may even accuse them of disloyalty,\N\N他们甚至责备孩子不忠,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.04,0:00:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or make some spiteful remark about the friends' parents.\N\N或者讲些小朋友家长的坏话.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a loss of dignity and descent into childish behaviour on the part of the adults\N\N家长这种有失身份和孩子气的作法aa\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,adolescent: n.  底毁\N\Ndeeply shocks the adolescents,and makes them resolve that in future\N\N使青春期的孩子大为震惊决心以后aa\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.13,0:00:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they will not talk to their parents about the places or people they visit.\N\N不再向父母讲述去过的地方和见过的人.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.88,0:01:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Before very long the parents will be complaining that the child is so secretive and never tells them anything,\N\N不要很久,家长就会抱怨孩子守口如瓶,什么事也不告诉他们,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.35,0:01:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but they seldom realize that they have brought this on themselves.\N\N殊不知这都是他们自己招致的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.71,0:01:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Disillusionment with the parents,\N\N孩子们对家长幻想的破灭\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.03,0:01:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,however good and adequate they may be both as parents and as individuals,\N\N不管家长的人品有多么好,作为父母又多么合格,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.13,0:01:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is to some degree inevitable.\N\N在某种程度上是不可避免的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.73,0:01:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Most children have such a high ideal of their parents,\N\N大多数孩子对父母估价过高,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.84,0:01:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,unless the parents themselves have been unsatisfactory,\N\N除非父母自身不能令人满意,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.22,0:01:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluation: n.  评价\N\Nthat it can hardly hope to stand up to a realistic evaluation.\N\N以致这种估价很难指望经受住现实的考验.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.94,0:01:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Parents would be greatly surprised and deeply touched if they realized\N\N如果家长们意识到下述几点,他们将会大为吃惊和深受感动的\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.78,0:01:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,infallibility: n.  一贯正确\N\Nhow much belief their children usually have in their character and infallibility,\N\N就是意识到孩子们通常是多么相信家长的品行和绝对正确,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.12,0:01:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and how much this faith means to a child.\N\N意识到孩子们的这种信念会对孩子产生多么大的影响.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.63,0:01:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,adolescent: n.  底毁\N\NIf parents were prepared for this adolescent reaction,\N\N如果家长对青少年的这种反应有思想准备,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.86,0:01:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and realized that was a sign that the child was growing up\N\N并且意识到这象征着孩子们正在成熟\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.14,0:02:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and developing valuable powers of observation and independent judgment,\N\N和正在发展宝贵的观察力独立判断力,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.98,0:02:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they would not be so hurt,\N\N那么他们就不会那样伤心\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.16,0:02:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,resent: v.  怨恨\N\Nand therefore would not drive the child into opposition by resenting and resisting it.\N\N也就不会由于怨恨和抵触这种反应,而把孩子推到自己的对立面去.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,adolescent: n.  底毁, sincerity: n.  诚挚\N\NThe adolescent,with his passion for sincerity,\N\N青少年酷爱真诚,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.57,0:02:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,always respects a parent who admits that he is wrong,or ignorant,\N\N他们总是尊敬能承认错误或无知\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.99,0:02:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,or even that he has been unfair or unjust.\N\N甚至自己做得不公平或不公正的父母.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.85,0:02:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What the child cannot forgive is\N\N孩子们所不能原谅的是:\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.96,0:02:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the parents' refusal to admit these charges if the child knows them to be true.\N\N父母错了,孩子们也看出来了,可是做父母的还不肯承认.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.15,0:02:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Victorian parents believed\N\N维多利亚时代的父母认为\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.59,0:02:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,retreat: v.  后退\N\Nthat they kept their dignity by retreating behind an unreasoning authoritarian attitude,\N\N他们可以靠无理的权威气派来维护自己的尊严,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.00,0:02:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact they did nothing of the kind,\N\N实际上那是根本不行的.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.56,0:02:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but children were then too cowed to let them know how they really felt.\N\N孩子们只不过被吓得不敢让父母知道自己的想法罢了.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we tend to go to the other extreme,\N\N虽然现在我们倾向于走向另一个极端,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.70,0:03:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but on the whole this is a healthier attitude both for the child and the parent.\N\N但总地来看,孩子和家长双方态度都比较端正.\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.79,0:03:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It is always wiser and safer to face up to reality,\N\N遇事采取面对现实的态度总是比较明智和稳妥的,\N\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.47,0:03:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,however painful it may be at the moment.\N\N尽管会有暂时的痛苦.\N\N